==English==

===Noun===
'''empiricism'''

# The method or practice of an [[empiric]]; pursuit of knowledge by [[observation]] and [[experiment]].
#*'''1951''' January 1, Albert Einstein, letter to Maurice Solovine, as published in ''Letters to Solovine'' (1993)
#*:I have found no better expression than "religious" for confidence in the rational nature of reality''...''. Whenever this feeling is absent, science degenerates into uninspired '''empiricism'''.
# Specifically, a practice of medicine founded on mere experience, without the aid of science or a knowledge of principles; ignorant and unscientific practice.
# The philosophical theory which attributes the origin of all our knowledge to experience.

====Synonyms====
*{{italbrac-colon|medical practice founded on experience}} [[charlatanry]], [[quackery]]

